Okmulgee FFA
August 31 at 5:24 PM ·

We are thrilled to announce that Okmulgee FFA has been awarded the prestigious National 3-Star Chapter Award from National FFA. It has been 46 YEARS since we have been awarded the NCA - back in 1974. This puts Okmulgee FFA in the top 32 chapters in Oklahoma and in the top 5% of chapters nationwide (8,700 chapters). Congrats Okmulgee FFA members!

shared_text:
Green Country Technology Center
August 13 at 12:11 PM ·

As we prepare for the return of full-time students to our campus, GCTC’s top priority is the safety and well being of our students, teachers, staff and all stakeholders. With that in mind, PHASE IV of our Mitigation Plan will follow the guidelines provided by the CDC as well as the Oklahoma State Department of Health’s COVID-19 Alert System.

PHASE IV will include all prior Phases I, II & III with the addition of the new Return to Learn Plans and guidelines which can be found on our website.

- GCTC’S COVID-19 Alert System color chart
- Student Guide Return to Learning – GREEN (New Normal)
- Student Guide Return to Learning – YELLOW (Low Risk)
- Student Guide Return to Learning – ORANGE (Moderate Risk)
- Student Guide Return to Learning – RED (High Risk)

Please note, when full-time classes begin on August 24, our school will begin in the ORANGE ZONE.

Please refer to our website for downloadable documents and details.

https://www.gctcok.edu/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1682277&type=d&pREC_ID=1862751

YES! During these unprecedented times (I’m getting tired of that phrase too) students who choose the online/virtual option for enrollment with Okmulgee High School or Dunbar (8th grade) can enroll in Agricultural Education classes. As long as they fully participate in class instruction and activities (physically and/or virtually) with Mr. Taylor, they can be members of FFA and everything AgEd has to offer. Select “AgEd” as an elective choice when filling out your pre-enrollment packet this year! If you (or parents) have any questions- reach out to Mr. Taylor. 💻 🌱💙💛

Why is the census important to me?

Responding to the census is not only your civic duty; it also affects the amount of funding your community receives, how your community plans for the future, and your representation in government. Specifically, data from the 2020 Census are used to:
• Ensure public services and funding for schools, hospitals, and fire departments.
• Plan new homes and businesses and improve neighborhoods.
Please take time to click the link and fill out the 2020 Census

Thursday, May 14th
8:00-10:00 PreK and Kindergarten
10:30-12:30 1st and 2nd grades

5:00-7:00. Open to All

Thank you for all you have done during this time of distance learning. We appreciate you!

shared_text:
Okmulgee Link Crew is with Mauricio Nix and 13 others at Okmulgee Board of Education.
May 5 at 11:50 AM · Okmulgee, OK ·

We are so very proud of our 2019-20 Senior Link Crew Leaders! Not only have these students navigated high school successfully but they chose to share their experiences and lessons learned with freshmen throughout the school year. They hosted movies with popcorn, a Christmas luncheon with individual gifts, took them bowling followed by lunch in the park, brought them donuts for breakfast, but most importantly, checked in with their freshmen on a regular basis to make sure they knew their Link Leaders were always there for them! Thank you, each one of you, for all that you did to make this school year a success for all students at OHS!
You will be missed!!
#OHSLinkCrew #boomboom

shared_text:
Okmulgee Dunbar School
May 4 at 7:51 AM ·

Happy National Teacher Appreciation Week!! Here at Okmulgee Schools, we take this opportunity to celebrate all of our faculty and staff. We couldn't do what we do without everybody working together. Thank you to the custodial staff for coming in early to get our buildings shined up and ready each day. Our kitchen staff for planning and preparing delicious meals and being some of the first people to interact with our students each morning. Our transportation staff for picking up and bringing so many of our kids to school safely and with a smile and greeting as they get not the bus. Our office staff for doing so much each day including answering questions, playing nurse, greeting everybody and even watching classes sometimes. Our teachers and teachers aides for working hands on with the students to insure they receive the best classroom experiences. To everyone behind the scenes, the maintenance crew and IT staff for handling all the daily trouble tickets to keep everything running smoothly. We appreciate every one of you. I'm proud to be a part of the #DunbarSquad.

Okmulgee Primary
March 28 at 9:20 AM ·

All total we had 40 teachers trying out Zoom video conferencing yesterday. Definitely not what we are used to, but a great way to check in on each other and begin planning for distance learning for our kiddos. Thankfully we anticipated that this might happen so before spring break each grade level gathered up some home learning lessons. Have no fear parents and students...we are going to have some things ready for you to do with your kiddos (and we think you just might have some fun while doing them).
#okmulgeeprimary
#weloveandmissourstudents
#ittakesavillage

shared_text:
Okmulgee Primary
March 18 at 9:52 AM ·

It may still be our scheduled spring break, but so many teachers and staff members have already mentioned how much they miss our students and wonder how they are doing.

Please let your children know that they are missed each and every day whether it's a school break or a health crisis requiring us to be closed for a time.

For right now no formal instruction is being sent home for students to work on, but there are so many things parents can do with their children during this time.

We will be sharing tips and ideas periodically for you to use at home. Some will be online resources and some will be things you can do around the house. Whatever you do, just take this time to enjoy spending time with your children.

Okmulgee High School
March 2 at 7:46 AM ·

Okmulgee split the speech team into two divisions in Tahlequah. We entered in 4A and the Champs division. We also had one novice in the novice division. Overall 27 entries advanced to semifinals and finals. Okmulgee gained 4 qualifications for regionals along with 10 medals.
Medals in champs included
3rd place
Shyla Tapp and Ariel Brown in humorous duet
Marissa Piza and Garrett Goddard in dramatic duet
Ryon Davis in LD debate
2nd place
Marissa Piza and Ryon Davis in humorous duet
Kandace Johnson in Monologue
1st place
Shyla Tapp and CheBonne BlueEagle in dramatic duet

Medals in 4A compeititon:
3rd place
Robert Marek in dramatic interpretation
Justice Holman in standard oratory
2nd place
Nicholae Adamson in Foreign extemp
Kandace Johnson in dramatic interpretation

Medal in novice competition
3rd
Gabrielle Miller in domestic extemp

Assistant coach Stormy Howell, Novice Coach Angela Johnson, and Coach Skyleen Willingham are now getting ready for NSDA Districts March 5-7, Regional OSSAA March 27-28, and OSSAA State April 16-18.

Mr. Taylor and Mrs. Johnson spent the last week at the 92nd National FFA Convention in Indianapolis sharing the message of Okmulgee FFA’s involvement with Microsoft Farmbeats Student Kits. At their booth in the FFA Blue Room, they visited with more than 400 students and advisors over three days and facilitated four Farmbeats workshops reaching an additional 300 students and advisors. Great experience to spread the word that #LifeIsGoodInOkmulgee. #FFA19

Okmulgee High School
October 15, 2019 at 10:34 AM ·

Okmulgee High School will be hosting another FAFSA Night this year for our 2019-2020 Seniors. Parents/Guardians please plan to attend with your child on Thursday, October 24th @ 5:00-7:30 PM. The FAFSA is required to be completed by any senior planning secondary education after high school. The free application qualifies a student for federal grants, work-study programs and student loans. With grants or loans, the money will be applied toward your child's tuition, fees and (if you live on campus) room and board.
